Postal questionnaires were sent to 308 clinicians in the UK (general 
practitioners, obstetricians, clinical geneticists, neurologists, 
paediatricians, and paediatric neurologists) to assess their knowledge of, and 
attitudes to, the prenatal diagnosis of three common single gene disorders, 
Huntington's disease (HD), cystic fibrosis (CF), and Duchenne muscular dystrophy 
